    "narrative": "For the Austin Waves on May 4, **Gunnar Henderson** stands as our premier play with a 68.83 score, benefiting from an favorable matchup against Schlittler and a robust 14% boost from his dynamic platoon advantage. He is closely shadowed by **Josh Lowe** (65.52), who sees a significant lift from an opposing xERA of 4.38; his aggressive upside makes him a core component of today's scoring potential. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.07) and **Heliot Ramos** (61.01) also rate as elite starts, with the latter capitalizing on an excellent 19% SP skill advantage against V\u00e1squez. While **Kyle Tucker** (58.09) faces a tougher matchup against Okert, his high base projection ensures he remains a vital fixture in our outfield.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's card centered on the utility slot. While **Nolan Schanuel** earned the final start with a 57.02 score due to his steady presence in the three-hole, he narrowly edged out several marginal options that fell below our efficiency thresholds. We remain cautious of **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks**, as both catchers face elite or near-elite arms in Gilbert and Nola, respectively, suppressing their scores to the mid-40s. With our top talent like **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, and **Jorge Polanco** sidelined on the IL, we are leaning heavily on the high-floor production of **Sam Antonacci** (55.41), whose leadoff positioning and 400 xwOBA provide the necessary stability to bridge the gap while we await the return of our core depth.",
